WEBVTT

00:00.715 --> 00:01.914
<i>Previously on "Too Close to Home"... </i>

00:03.344 --> 00:05.078
- So, where you been?
- Oh, I just had to stay late.

00:05.080 --> 00:07.080
We cannot go and jeopardize her job.

00:07.082 --> 00:09.149
She works in the White House.

00:09.151 --> 00:10.917
<i>The president suffered a heart attack.</i>

00:10.919 --> 00:12.953
Katelynn: You're a lying
bit of trailer park trash

00:12.955 --> 00:14.321
from happy, Alabama.

00:14.323 --> 00:16.423
Tomorrow, the world will know
about you and him.

00:16.425 --> 00:18.925
Woman: <i>Her name is Annie Belle Hayes.</i>

00:18.927 --> 00:20.627
<i>Allegedly she was having an affair</i>

00:20.629 --> 00:22.462
<i>with President Christian.</i>

00:22.464 --> 00:25.065
You wanted my sister.
You didn't want me.

00:26.401 --> 00:27.567
Shelby!

00:27.569 --> 00:28.802
Your sister took my load.

00:28.804 --> 00:29.803
She took both your loads.

00:29.805 --> 00:31.104
He drives for an electronics company,

00:31.106 --> 00:33.106
so I know there's all kinds
of TVs and computers in there.

00:35.677 --> 00:38.078
Man: You got 24 hours
to get me my package

00:38.080 --> 00:39.946
or Bonnie and Shelby gonna be killed.

00:39.948 --> 00:41.514
What the hell kind of sister are you?

00:41.516 --> 00:43.783
The type that doesn't sleep
with her sister's boyfriend.

00:43.785 --> 00:44.851
You think that you're just going to go?

00:44.853 --> 00:46.920
Damn. There's nothing here.

00:46.922 --> 00:48.121
This is happy, Alabama.

00:48.123 --> 00:49.756
- Can I come in?
- No.

00:49.758 --> 00:50.824
I heard some things.

00:50.826 --> 00:52.325
I'm sure you have.

00:52.327 --> 00:54.027
A lot has changed since
you walked out on me.

00:54.029 --> 00:55.762
You left us here to fend for ourselves.

00:55.764 --> 00:58.031
You can't give us a damn dime.

00:58.033 --> 00:59.866
[Voice breaking] I don't know you.

00:59.868 --> 01:01.701
I don't know where I am.

01:01.703 --> 01:03.003
It's okay, Daddy.

01:03.005 --> 01:05.438
Maybe I'll take home one
of these fine country boys

01:05.440 --> 01:07.374
and let them show me
a good time tonight.

01:07.376 --> 01:09.175
Victor!
[Grunting]

01:09.177 --> 01:11.378
Man, he looks really bad.
Can your daddy help him?

01:11.380 --> 01:14.180
- Give him two CC's of this.
- [Gasps]

01:14.182 --> 01:15.167
Why is she here?

01:15.168 --> 01:16.225
Taking care of you.

01:16.226 --> 01:17.181
Daddy, no!

01:17.182 --> 01:18.302
He's alive.

01:18.303 --> 01:19.702
- He saved him.
- Hi.

01:19.703 --> 01:21.603
- Where's Victor?
- What's wrong?

01:21.604 --> 01:22.670
<i>You're</i> what's wrong.

01:22.671 --> 01:23.483
Brody. Annie's here.

01:23.484 --> 01:24.514
Is Brody seeing anybody?

01:24.515 --> 01:26.615
Bonnie: No?

01:28.219 --> 01:29.351
Hi.

01:29.353 --> 01:30.486
Hi.

01:30.488 --> 01:32.221
- You still love her.
- No, I don't.

01:32.223 --> 01:33.222
Yeah, you do.

01:33.224 --> 01:34.523
The press haunts us,

01:34.525 --> 01:36.058
ever since you brought them
back to his place.

01:36.060 --> 01:37.359
They follow us like we did it.

01:37.361 --> 01:38.527
I need you to go
to the bank with me,

01:38.529 --> 01:39.695
and I need to put this house up.

01:39.697 --> 01:40.696
That's not happening.

01:40.698 --> 01:42.465
Mama left me her share.

01:42.467 --> 01:43.566
And my daddy has the other half.

01:43.568 --> 01:45.868
I can't let go of what he did to me.

01:45.870 --> 01:47.136
You both should have stopped him.

01:47.138 --> 01:48.704
I did stop him!

01:48.706 --> 01:51.040
You didn't have to have a baby with him.

01:51.042 --> 01:53.642
Yes, I did! We all did!

01:53.644 --> 01:55.444
I can't look at my daughter

01:55.446 --> 01:57.379
any more than you can
look at your own son.

01:57.381 --> 01:59.982
The load on his truck.
What did you do with it?

01:59.984 --> 02:01.217
I sold it, all right?

02:01.219 --> 02:02.251
J.B.

02:02.253 --> 02:03.519
No, no! No!

02:03.521 --> 02:05.988
[Screaming]

02:13.531 --> 02:15.898
[Gunshots]

02:15.900 --> 02:17.933
[Screaming]

02:17.935 --> 02:20.102
[Glass shattering]

02:25.009 --> 02:26.675
[Dogs barking]

02:26.677 --> 02:28.677
[Shattering continues]

02:31.115 --> 02:32.948
[Tires screech]

02:32.950 --> 02:35.584
[Screaming]

02:35.586 --> 02:36.852
[Tires screech]

02:36.854 --> 02:39.822
[Dog barking]

02:41.000 --> 02:47.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:48.366 --> 02:50.533
[Dog barking in distance]

02:54.138 --> 02:56.672
[TV playing indistinctly]

03:02.747 --> 03:05.848
[Gunshots]

03:05.850 --> 03:08.217
[Machine gunfire]

03:08.219 --> 03:09.985
[Dog barking]

03:09.987 --> 03:12.688
[Gunshot, tires screech]

03:12.690 --> 03:14.723
[Barking continues]

03:14.725 --> 03:16.625
[Tires screech]

03:16.627 --> 03:18.961
[Engine revs]

03:20.097 --> 03:21.897
[Barking continues]

03:29.026 --> 03:31.026
_

03:31.757 --> 03:34.825
♪ Too close to home ♪

03:34.827 --> 03:38.295
[Dog barking]

03:40.199 --> 03:41.398
You okay?

03:41.400 --> 03:42.399
- I'm fine.
- You all right?

03:42.401 --> 03:43.867
- I'm fine.
- Annie!

03:43.869 --> 03:45.235
I'm okay. I'm okay.

03:45.237 --> 03:46.737
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

03:46.739 --> 03:48.739
Mom! Mama!

03:48.750 --> 03:50.150
Are you all right?!

03:50.530 --> 03:52.396
Oh, my god!

03:52.398 --> 03:54.165
[Panting]

03:54.167 --> 03:56.233
- Are you all right?
- No, no! Get away from me!

03:56.235 --> 03:58.135
- What's wrong?
- This is all her fault!

03:58.137 --> 03:59.737
Hey, hey, hey, hey! Come here.

03:59.739 --> 04:01.272
You stop that right now, all right?

04:01.274 --> 04:02.673
I don't want to hear it.

04:02.675 --> 04:04.108
- Bonnie, you almost died.
- All right, listen to me.

04:04.110 --> 04:05.409
- I'm gonna go check on Mama.
- Bonnie, who was that?

04:05.411 --> 04:07.411
All right? Just stay here.

04:07.413 --> 04:09.880
[Door opens]

04:09.882 --> 04:11.615
Bonnie, what the hell is going on?

04:11.617 --> 04:12.650
- Call the sheriff.
- I already...

04:12.652 --> 04:14.185
- Call the sheriff!
- I already did!

04:14.187 --> 04:16.353
- This is crazy!
- What is going on?

04:16.355 --> 04:17.887
- We could have been killed!
- I know it!

04:17.890 --> 04:20.558
- Mama, you all right?
- Yeah! What happened?!

04:20.560 --> 04:22.993
- Are you hurt?
- I'm fine. Tell me what happened.

04:22.995 --> 04:25.162
[Sighs]
It's... it's over now, okay?

04:25.164 --> 04:27.097
Well, that's not telling me
what happened, girl!

04:27.099 --> 04:29.567
When your brother gets back
here, we are moving.

04:29.569 --> 04:31.802
Moving?! Moving where, Regina?!

04:31.804 --> 04:33.871
He's in the army! It ain't
like he's making millions!

04:33.873 --> 04:35.239
I don't like it here!

04:35.241 --> 04:36.674
Well, you married him,

04:36.676 --> 04:38.008
so you just gonna have to
deal with it!

04:38.010 --> 04:39.076
- Deal with it?!
- Deal with it!

04:39.078 --> 04:40.845
- There were bullets flying!
- Calm down!

04:40.847 --> 04:42.179
No, you the one always so dramatic!

04:42.181 --> 04:43.948
I mean it! Calm down!

04:43.950 --> 04:46.183
- You all right?
- They're all right, Elm.

04:46.185 --> 04:47.551
You sure?

04:51.090 --> 04:53.924
I'm your wife. Worry about <i> me.</i>

04:53.926 --> 04:55.526
[Scoffs]
Damn, Tina.

04:55.528 --> 04:57.294
He's just trying
to check up on us.

04:57.296 --> 04:59.396
Well, I'm his wife.

04:59.398 --> 05:00.464
I'm sorry.

05:05.271 --> 05:07.371
She is such a bitch.

05:07.373 --> 05:10.307
Don't nobody want him.
I mean, look at him.

05:12.879 --> 05:16.580
You know, I bet this got
something to do with her.

05:16.582 --> 05:18.549
- Who?
- Her.

05:20.253 --> 05:22.853
She don't never talk to nobody.

05:22.855 --> 05:25.022
- Moved up in here.
- Says she go to work.

05:25.024 --> 05:27.658
She don't ever be in town.

05:27.660 --> 05:30.427
♪♪

05:36.238 --> 05:39.072
She don't talk to me. She talk to you?

05:39.074 --> 05:41.775
[Clicks tongue] Girl, will you
stop it and get on in this house?

05:41.777 --> 05:44.811
Lord, I'm just glad
my kids weren't here.

05:44.813 --> 05:45.812
Where are they?

05:45.814 --> 05:46.880
Uh, Johnny got them.

05:46.882 --> 05:48.715
He said he's bringing them back later.

05:50.085 --> 05:51.318
I'll be back, all right?

05:51.320 --> 05:53.453
No, listen! It's that
damn sister of yours!

05:53.455 --> 05:55.722
She's gonna get us all killed!
All of us!

05:55.724 --> 05:58.625
I saw them men with my mirrors
in the secret service!

05:58.627 --> 06:00.060
Secret service, Mama?

06:00.062 --> 06:02.128
I saw them! I did!

06:02.130 --> 06:03.997
I got to go, okay?

06:03.999 --> 06:05.098
Bonnie, please!

06:05.100 --> 06:06.733
I'm telling you it's your damn sister!

06:06.735 --> 06:07.801
I'll be back.

06:07.803 --> 06:09.636
Come on, now, Bonnie!

06:11.573 --> 06:12.639
[Door slams]

06:12.641 --> 06:16.309
I swear them damn folks is from D.C.

06:19.414 --> 06:22.015
Howard: Your vitals are
looking really good.

06:22.017 --> 06:24.117
And why am I so tired?

06:24.119 --> 06:26.386
It's the meds.

06:26.388 --> 06:27.988
[Sighs]

06:27.990 --> 06:30.290
Howard, what the hell happened?

06:30.292 --> 06:31.925
You had a heart attack.

06:31.927 --> 06:33.026
I didn't have a heart attack.

06:33.028 --> 06:34.528
Yes, sir, you did.

06:34.530 --> 06:36.162
How the hell is that possible?

06:36.164 --> 06:38.665
That's what we're trying to find out.

06:38.667 --> 06:40.800
[Sighs]

06:40.802 --> 06:42.969
Does the country know?

06:42.971 --> 06:44.638
Yes.

06:44.640 --> 06:45.906
Damn it.

06:45.908 --> 06:48.608
Don't be upset.
It's being handled and managed.

06:48.610 --> 06:50.710
This is not good.

06:50.712 --> 06:52.045
I need to address the nation.

06:52.047 --> 06:53.713
Yes, I know, but not
before you're better.

06:53.715 --> 06:55.382
Now.

06:55.384 --> 06:56.883
No, sir.

06:56.885 --> 06:58.752
Let me look at the tests
in the morning, and we'll talk.

06:58.754 --> 07:00.387
Howard, I am fine.

07:00.389 --> 07:03.089
Mr. President, you have to
take this seriously.

07:03.091 --> 07:06.092
How the hell did this happen?

07:08.430 --> 07:10.697
I think I know.

07:10.699 --> 07:13.166
Did you take the pills I gave you?

07:13.168 --> 07:14.868
Yes.

07:14.870 --> 07:16.836
Are you saying that's what caused it?

07:16.838 --> 07:18.772
No, no, no. You're the
picture of health.

07:18.774 --> 07:20.540
The dosage you were taking is mild.

07:20.542 --> 07:22.642
It couldn't have caused it.

07:22.644 --> 07:24.377
Something did.

07:24.379 --> 07:26.346
And you took only one?

07:26.348 --> 07:27.914
Yes.

07:27.916 --> 07:29.983
Where are they?

07:29.985 --> 07:31.885
My desk in the Oval.

07:31.887 --> 07:34.321
Can you get me in to get them?

07:34.323 --> 07:36.723
What do you mean, can I get you in?

07:36.725 --> 07:38.258
The Vice President has taken the, um...

07:38.260 --> 07:40.126
Don't you say that to me.

07:40.128 --> 07:42.495
You get his ass in here,
let him know that I'm fine.

07:42.497 --> 07:43.730
- Yes, sir.
- I'm fine.

07:43.732 --> 07:46.032
Where's my Press Secretary?

07:46.034 --> 07:47.467
Where's my Chief of Staff?

07:47.469 --> 07:48.935
I want their asses in here...
[Coughs]

07:48.937 --> 07:50.537
Calm down, sir. Please calm down.

07:50.539 --> 07:52.505
Don't you tell me to calm down!

07:52.507 --> 07:54.207
Get them here now!

07:54.209 --> 07:56.676
[Coughs]

08:00.616 --> 08:02.582
[Door opens]

08:05.354 --> 08:06.853
He's asleep. [Door closes]

08:10.392 --> 08:12.092
I can't wait for him to get better

08:12.094 --> 08:15.028
so that we can get the hell
out of here and get back to D.C.

08:15.030 --> 08:19.399
There's something good
waiting for you there?

08:19.401 --> 08:22.369
Anywhere's better than here.

08:22.371 --> 08:24.704
It's not that bad.

08:24.706 --> 08:26.740
Are we in the same place?

08:26.742 --> 08:28.575
This place smells like cow [Bleep]

08:28.577 --> 08:32.712
You know, I've never seen you like this.

08:32.714 --> 08:34.414
Like what?

08:34.416 --> 08:37.183
This much of a bitch.

08:37.184 --> 08:40.053
What's wrong? Why are you so angry?

08:40.054 --> 08:41.254
Hello?

08:41.256 --> 08:43.356
This girl just cost us to lose our jobs.

08:43.357 --> 08:46.326
No, no, that's not it.
There's more to it.

08:48.263 --> 08:50.730
[Sighs]

08:50.732 --> 08:53.466
Dax, I have had to work
so much harder than you or her

08:53.468 --> 08:54.601
to get here.

08:54.603 --> 08:57.270
I didn't have a choice.

08:57.272 --> 09:02.609
Is this where I hear the "I'm a
poor black woman" speech again?

09:02.611 --> 09:04.310
Yeah.

09:04.312 --> 09:06.446
This is when this "poor black woman"

09:06.448 --> 09:07.914
slaps the hell out of you.

09:07.916 --> 09:09.716
Now apologize.

09:09.718 --> 09:11.184
I'm sorry.

09:11.186 --> 09:13.586
I'm a bit on edge, too. I'm sorry.

09:13.588 --> 09:15.855
But you are very angry.

09:15.857 --> 09:17.490
I just told you why.

09:17.492 --> 09:19.259
Oh, no, no, no.

09:19.261 --> 09:21.661
There's something more to it than that.

09:21.663 --> 09:23.997
I'm just mad at her, okay?

09:23.999 --> 09:25.432
I mean, look at what she did to Victor.

09:25.434 --> 09:26.666
She didn't do that!

09:26.668 --> 09:28.435
Shh.

09:28.437 --> 09:30.103
She might as well have.

09:30.105 --> 09:33.239
Look, he'll be okay, and
then we can get out of here

09:33.241 --> 09:36.443
and return to the hell of
what used to be our lives.

09:36.445 --> 09:38.278
What's left of it.

09:40.348 --> 09:43.216
Is there anybody from the
White House that you can call?

09:43.218 --> 09:45.351
Nobody's answering me.

09:45.353 --> 09:47.921
I know a few people.

09:47.923 --> 09:52.058
Well, can you just find out,
you know, how he's doing?

09:53.962 --> 09:55.228
Why?

09:55.230 --> 09:56.796
I just want to know.

09:56.798 --> 09:58.665
He's the President.

09:58.667 --> 10:00.400
Uh-huh.

10:00.402 --> 10:02.902
Yeah. I'll call someone.

10:04.361 --> 10:05.593
Who?

10:05.595 --> 10:07.562
I don't know.

10:07.564 --> 10:09.631
Maybe Marnie.

10:09.633 --> 10:10.857
No.

10:10.859 --> 10:12.158
They've already made it clear that

10:12.160 --> 10:14.227
we are not to talk to
anybody in the White House.

10:14.229 --> 10:16.429
I know.

10:21.346 --> 10:23.380
I just want to get out of here.

10:25.617 --> 10:30.153
Although I wouldn't mind staying
around to keep an eye on <i> him.</i>

10:30.155 --> 10:32.355
He's gorgeous.

10:32.357 --> 10:34.791
Yeah. I'll take Victor.

10:34.793 --> 10:35.992
Oh, come on.

10:35.994 --> 10:37.794
Don't act like you don't
have the hots for this guy.

10:37.796 --> 10:40.063
Hmm, not my type.

10:40.065 --> 10:41.831
Why would he stay here?

10:41.833 --> 10:44.601
Why not move to D.C. or New York?

10:44.603 --> 10:46.303
Hell, L.A.

10:46.305 --> 10:47.971
Why don't you ask him?

10:47.973 --> 10:51.074
You know what? I think I will.

10:52.277 --> 10:54.311
[Cellphone rings]

10:54.313 --> 10:55.779
That's the White House.

10:55.781 --> 10:57.314
No, it's not.

10:57.316 --> 11:00.717
Dax, I know that ring. We both have it.

11:00.719 --> 11:02.752
It's the White House.

11:04.189 --> 11:06.056
Marnie.

11:06.058 --> 11:07.490
Do not tell her anything.

11:07.492 --> 11:09.059
I won't.

11:10.829 --> 11:12.262
Take it.

11:12.264 --> 11:13.496
Excuse me?

11:13.498 --> 11:14.497
Take the call.

11:14.499 --> 11:16.466
Okay, okay.

11:16.468 --> 11:18.234
Where are you going?

11:18.236 --> 11:19.235
I'll fill you in.

11:19.237 --> 11:20.971
Hold, please.

11:22.274 --> 11:24.107
[Door opens]

11:27.271 --> 11:28.637
Yeah.

11:28.639 --> 11:31.040
Katelynn: What are you doing there?

11:31.042 --> 11:32.941
I'm in Alabama.

11:32.943 --> 11:34.910
Alabama? Yes, I know.

11:34.912 --> 11:36.912
But what I don't know
is why you are there.

11:36.914 --> 11:38.047
That was the question.

11:38.049 --> 11:40.649
Well, uh, Victor decided to drive down.

11:40.651 --> 11:43.552
I know. He was assaulted
by some country hicks.

11:43.554 --> 11:44.987
Boo hoo.

11:44.989 --> 11:47.990
I need you to get your ass back
here to help me deal with this.

11:47.992 --> 11:49.491
Well, I was fired.

11:49.493 --> 11:51.794
Not anymore. I need you here.

11:52.998 --> 11:55.798
Katelynn, please, I can't just...

11:55.800 --> 11:58.468
Am I not clear?
This is both of our mess.

11:58.470 --> 11:59.969
Oh, don't you dare.

11:59.971 --> 12:01.471
I didn't have anything to do with this.

12:01.501 --> 12:04.068
You know better than
to speak to me on this phone.

12:04.070 --> 12:05.870
How is he?

12:05.872 --> 12:07.805
[Sighs] He's recovering.

12:07.807 --> 12:09.908
Okay, well, that's good.

12:09.910 --> 12:12.543
Did you really just say that to me?

12:12.574 --> 12:14.741
So you went down to
Alabama for that whore

12:14.743 --> 12:15.876
that I ran out of this town

12:15.878 --> 12:18.345
with her tail tucked between her legs?

12:19.698 --> 12:23.834
No. Victor decided to drive her
down here, and he got beat up.

12:23.836 --> 12:26.136
Yes, and the assault
has left him in the bed.

12:26.138 --> 12:28.972
- I can't just...
- Check your e-mail now.

12:28.974 --> 12:31.975
♪♪

12:45.424 --> 12:47.991
That was two days before he left.

12:49.595 --> 12:51.762
Do you recognize the guy?

12:51.764 --> 12:53.964
He's a senator.

12:56.335 --> 12:59.102
He's planning on trading up, my friend,

12:59.104 --> 13:01.805
leaving you out in the cold.

13:01.807 --> 13:04.975
You thought your little boy
toy had gone straight?

13:04.977 --> 13:07.611
No pun intended.

13:07.613 --> 13:09.546
Well, he hasn't.

13:09.548 --> 13:12.749
I know you, Dax. Believe me,
those dates are correct.

13:12.751 --> 13:14.184
Now, forget about him.

13:14.186 --> 13:16.052
Leave him there and get back here.

13:16.054 --> 13:18.622
We need to move on to plan "B."

13:22.895 --> 13:24.861
[Phone hangs up]

13:29.168 --> 13:31.268
[Cellphone beeps]

13:36.108 --> 13:37.974
[Sniffles]

13:37.976 --> 13:39.876
[Cellphone beeps]

13:39.878 --> 13:42.379
[Ringing]

13:42.381 --> 13:44.915
- Woman: Immigration office.

13:44.917 --> 13:47.884
I need to speak to Al Monroe, please.

13:47.886 --> 13:48.952
Just a moment.

13:48.954 --> 13:50.086
[Beeping]

13:50.088 --> 13:51.888
- Al: Al Monroe.
- Al, it's Dax.

13:51.890 --> 13:54.758
Hey. I heard you were fired. So sorry.

13:54.760 --> 13:56.927
Yeah, don't count on it.

13:56.929 --> 13:58.795
What's going on?

14:01.133 --> 14:03.166
Dax?

14:04.369 --> 14:05.936
I need some people deported.

14:05.938 --> 14:08.338
Dax, you know I-I-I can't do that.

14:08.340 --> 14:11.208
Do you want me to have
a conversation with your wife?

14:11.210 --> 14:12.843
No, no. No.

14:14.012 --> 14:16.313
Then you know what you need to do.

14:18.750 --> 14:20.484
Names?

14:27.926 --> 14:29.759
Dax, you know...

14:29.761 --> 14:32.762
♪♪

14:37.536 --> 14:38.902
[Engine shuts off]

14:43.041 --> 14:44.774
- Hey.
- Hi.

14:44.776 --> 14:46.209
Is everything all right at the trailer?

14:46.211 --> 14:47.911
- Yeah, yeah.
- What's going on?

14:47.913 --> 14:49.379
I tried calling you.

14:49.381 --> 14:50.981
Yeah, well, my phone's
in the truck. What's up?

14:50.983 --> 14:52.649
Something happened over there.

14:52.651 --> 14:53.984
- What?
- I don't know.

14:53.986 --> 14:55.986
Just a car hit a tree, then
the sheriff went flying past me.

14:55.988 --> 14:57.354
I mean, you don't think that...

14:57.356 --> 14:58.722
No. No.

14:58.724 --> 15:00.056
Look, are you sure?

15:00.058 --> 15:01.558
Yes. I'm sure, all right?

15:01.560 --> 15:03.426
Let me go check it out.
Go on inside, all right?

15:03.428 --> 15:04.828
Okay. All right, thank you.

15:04.830 --> 15:06.630
Hey, Dax, this is Frankie.

15:06.632 --> 15:07.731
- Hi.
- Hi.

15:07.733 --> 15:08.832
All right, keep an eye on her, please.

15:08.834 --> 15:10.534
- I'll be right back.
- Keep an eye on her?

15:10.536 --> 15:12.702
What? Are you 12?

15:12.704 --> 15:15.872
He's just... He's a bit protective.

15:15.874 --> 15:17.040
[Engine starts]

15:17.042 --> 15:18.575
Of course he is.

15:28.294 --> 15:30.027
[Door opens]

15:42.609 --> 15:44.075
Hi.

15:43.659 --> 15:44.658
How is he?

15:44.660 --> 15:46.727
He's good. He's, uh, better.

15:46.729 --> 15:48.462
Oh, that's good to hear.

15:48.464 --> 15:50.431
- He's sedated.
- Sedated?

15:50.433 --> 15:52.333
Yes. Uh, would you like me to wake him?

15:52.335 --> 15:54.668
- He may be a little groggy.
- Oh, no. Let him rest.

15:54.670 --> 15:57.671
Um, he's been through quite the ordeal.

15:57.673 --> 16:00.641
Yes, he has, but he's a strong man.

16:00.643 --> 16:03.210
Yes, but I'm confused.

16:03.212 --> 16:05.546
How could you not foresee this?

16:06.816 --> 16:09.083
Well, there's nothing
in his medical history

16:09.085 --> 16:11.886
or recent exams
to suggest a heart attack.

16:11.888 --> 16:14.355
Even sexual stimulants?

16:14.357 --> 16:16.290
[Coughs]

16:16.292 --> 16:18.826
Come on, Howard.
Don't look so shocked.

16:18.828 --> 16:20.895
- Mrs... .
- I know you provide them for him.

16:22.298 --> 16:24.265
Mrs. Christian.

16:24.267 --> 16:27.701
Oh, don't tell me his penis is
a matter of national security.

16:27.703 --> 16:29.537
Ma'am.

16:29.539 --> 16:33.808
Do you or do you not provide him
with sexual stimulants?

16:36.012 --> 16:38.512
I think that may be a question
for your husband.

16:38.514 --> 16:41.615
[Scoffs] I think you just answered it.

16:43.052 --> 16:45.319
[Sighs] If you'll excuse me.

16:45.321 --> 16:48.956
So, could they have caused this?

16:48.958 --> 16:50.891
I-I don't know how he could have...

16:50.893 --> 16:54.295
Stop trying to cover your ass
and answer the question.

16:56.966 --> 16:58.599
It's possible.

17:00.636 --> 17:02.269
Okay.

17:04.240 --> 17:06.973
Even if he had a dosage,
I'm sure it was only nominal.

17:06.976 --> 17:08.843
So he just wanted that extra stamina

17:08.845 --> 17:11.345
to keep up with his young conquest.

17:11.347 --> 17:14.515
I'm sorry, ma'am.
I-I know nothing of this matter.

17:14.517 --> 17:16.684
Sure you don't.

17:16.685 --> 17:18.252
If you would like the, um...

17:18.253 --> 17:21.689
No, what I would like
is for you to leave us, please.

17:21.691 --> 17:22.990
Leave us now.

17:22.992 --> 17:26.026
♪♪

17:32.768 --> 17:34.969
[Door opens]

17:34.971 --> 17:36.904
[Door closes]

17:38.975 --> 17:41.675
I'm sorry. Did I wake you?

17:43.479 --> 17:45.012
Hi.

17:45.014 --> 17:46.847
"Hi"?

17:46.849 --> 17:49.149
Is that all you have to say to me?

17:50.419 --> 17:52.353
I'm sorry. I was having a nightmare.

17:52.355 --> 17:54.622
- [Clears throat]
- No, you weren't.

17:54.624 --> 17:57.691
I'm not a dream. I'm real.

17:59.729 --> 18:01.128
I have to get up.

18:01.130 --> 18:02.863
No, no, no. You can't.

18:02.865 --> 18:06.734
You're on bed rest from
your heart attack, remember?

18:06.736 --> 18:08.769
[Sighs] I didn't have a heart attack.

18:08.771 --> 18:12.473
Yes, you did, according to
the doctors and the press.

18:14.310 --> 18:16.143
Did you slap me?

18:16.145 --> 18:18.012
Yes.

18:18.014 --> 18:20.047
Would you like another?

18:20.049 --> 18:21.916
Get out of here.

18:21.918 --> 18:23.417
Okay.

18:23.419 --> 18:25.853
But if I do, I'm going
to the yellow room

18:25.855 --> 18:27.655
to sit down with Primetime Leslie

18:27.657 --> 18:31.458
and tell the world that you were
in that room, the Oval,

18:31.460 --> 18:35.462
having sex with that girl,
sprawled across history.

18:38.167 --> 18:40.401
Have you no decency?

18:40.403 --> 18:43.570
I said get out of here.

18:43.572 --> 18:46.540
You know she's gone, right?

18:47.910 --> 18:49.176
What did you do?

18:49.178 --> 18:51.679
I chased her out of my town.

18:51.681 --> 18:55.549
Leave it to me to clean up after
your mess time and time again.

18:55.551 --> 18:58.585
I mean, how many times will I have
to put up with these whores, Thomas?

18:58.587 --> 19:00.154
How many times?

19:00.156 --> 19:03.524
I've threatened, I've warned,
I've threatened to walk,

19:03.526 --> 19:06.527
and you continue to do what you do.

19:06.529 --> 19:08.896
You continue to... why?

19:08.898 --> 19:10.764
Where is she?

19:10.766 --> 19:12.333
Don't tell me you care about this one.

19:12.335 --> 19:13.634
Well, you must.

19:13.636 --> 19:15.302
She had the nicest apartment, after all.

19:15.304 --> 19:16.637
Where is she, Katelynn?

19:16.639 --> 19:18.439
What's the last you remember?

19:18.441 --> 19:19.840
I'm not playing around with you!

19:19.842 --> 19:21.308
Ooh, watch your temper.

19:21.310 --> 19:23.711
You're not supposed to
get upset, remember?

19:25.548 --> 19:28.615
Now, what is the last thing
you remember?

19:28.617 --> 19:31.418
Let me refresh your memory.

19:31.420 --> 19:34.621
You were in the Oval
having sex with her,

19:34.623 --> 19:37.992
but two hours before that,
you had taken a pill.

19:37.994 --> 19:39.893
Not the ones from Dr. Craig,

19:39.895 --> 19:42.529
but the ones that I had
replaced them with,

19:42.531 --> 19:44.798
ones that are much higher dose.

19:49.805 --> 19:52.239
Are you telling me you tried to kill me?

19:52.241 --> 19:53.374
Yes.

19:53.376 --> 19:55.376
And I was supposed to
be the grieving wife,

19:55.378 --> 19:59.246
but, unfortunately, you made it.

19:59.248 --> 20:00.981
I will have you brought up on charges!

20:00.983 --> 20:04.618
Well, you think you can do that,
but I'm the wife.

20:04.620 --> 20:08.288
The wife is the vault.
All those secrets.

20:09.458 --> 20:11.959
25 years is a long time.

20:11.961 --> 20:15.129
So with me, please.

20:15.131 --> 20:16.497
Enough.

20:16.499 --> 20:18.799
You understand, Thomas?

20:18.801 --> 20:20.501
Enough of this.

20:20.503 --> 20:23.370
[Sighs]

20:24.348 --> 20:25.914
I'm just glad my kids
weren't here for this.

20:26.780 --> 20:29.214
Yeah, we don't normally have this
kind of thing going on around here.

20:30.855 --> 20:33.622
We sure don't. Something going on.

20:33.624 --> 20:37.026
Yeah, I know there is, Octavia.
It's obvious.

20:37.028 --> 20:40.129
Baby, you got to get me out of here.

20:40.131 --> 20:42.731
- I-I know.
- When you coming home?

20:42.733 --> 20:44.800
Soon, baby. Soon.

20:44.801 --> 20:46.267
I hate it here.

20:46.268 --> 20:47.868
I know, and I'm gonna
get us out of there.

20:47.869 --> 20:50.270
I'm just here staying with your sister.

20:50.271 --> 20:52.138
I mean, just... [Scoffs]

20:52.213 --> 20:54.012
Don't you love me?

20:54.014 --> 20:55.973
Yes, I love you, but I'm just saying.

20:55.975 --> 20:57.975
It's not easy.

20:57.977 --> 20:59.376
All right, I'll... I'll be there soon.

20:59.378 --> 21:01.145
I got to go back to the barracks.

21:01.147 --> 21:02.346
Baby.

21:02.348 --> 21:04.715
I'm sorry, baby. I'm sorry.

21:04.717 --> 21:06.050
Bye.

21:06.052 --> 21:07.651
- All right.
- Just bye.

21:07.653 --> 21:09.186
[Cellphone beeps]

21:09.188 --> 21:10.487
You shouldn't do that to him.

21:10.489 --> 21:12.456
Don't tell me what not to do.

21:12.458 --> 21:14.858
He's already torn up
being away from you.

21:14.860 --> 21:16.593
You just making it worse.

21:16.595 --> 21:18.729
Can you mind your business?

21:18.731 --> 21:21.632
You do know this is
my damn trailer, right?

21:21.634 --> 21:23.967
Girl, bye.

21:23.969 --> 21:26.136
Sheriff! Sheriff Mobley!

21:26.138 --> 21:27.671
Sheriff, what the hell is going on?

21:27.673 --> 21:29.740
I'm on it, honey. I'm on it.

21:29.742 --> 21:33.310
Now, what the hell happened here?

21:33.312 --> 21:34.845
You gonna tell him, J.B.?

21:34.847 --> 21:37.247
What's there to tell?

21:37.249 --> 21:38.716
Well, you can start by telling me

21:38.718 --> 21:40.617
who the hell that is
in that van over there.

21:40.619 --> 21:42.152
I don't know.

21:42.154 --> 21:44.121
Yeah, you do.

21:44.123 --> 21:45.589
Bonnie?

21:45.591 --> 21:46.924
I didn't see him.

21:46.926 --> 21:49.727
That's the same guy that told me
his name was Marty Doe.

21:49.729 --> 21:51.462
Now, what the hell's going on?

21:51.464 --> 21:52.796
J.B.

21:52.798 --> 21:54.631
There ain't... ain't nothing
going on, all right?

21:54.633 --> 21:56.033
Nothing... Nothing at all.

21:56.035 --> 21:58.435
Well, if that was the case, that
man wouldn't be over there dead,

21:58.437 --> 21:59.536
now, would he, J.B.?

21:59.538 --> 22:01.105
You tell him right now. You hear me?

22:01.107 --> 22:02.339
You tell him or I will!

22:02.341 --> 22:03.607
- Shut your mouth, baby!
- You can go...

22:03.609 --> 22:04.675
Shelby, it's 'cause of you!

22:04.677 --> 22:06.343
And you could have got
us all killed, J.B.!

22:06.345 --> 22:07.978
Yeah, well, the only thing
that I care about

22:07.980 --> 22:09.847
is this one right here
getting shot through the heart.

22:09.849 --> 22:11.115
Don't you talk to her like that!

22:11.117 --> 22:12.549
You're the one that got
her into this mess!

22:12.551 --> 22:13.684
- What the hell happened?!
- There is...

22:13.686 --> 22:15.018
There is nothing to tell, Mobley!

22:15.020 --> 22:16.420
He had drugs in his truck!

22:16.422 --> 22:17.421
- What?!
- You shut...

22:17.423 --> 22:18.589
- You shut your mouth, girl.
- Hey!

22:18.591 --> 22:19.857
Come on. You touch her, I swear.

22:19.859 --> 22:21.725
J.B., I swear.
You ain't gonna touch nobody.

22:21.727 --> 22:23.260
I'm right here.

22:23.262 --> 22:26.430
Sheriff, this is what happened.
J.B. Had a truck full of drugs.

22:26.432 --> 22:28.265
Shelby didn't know. She stole it.

22:28.267 --> 22:30.901
And she sold it to Xray and his boys.

22:30.903 --> 22:33.904
[Chuckles] You're going to jail, son.

22:33.906 --> 22:35.272
[Laughing] Oh, hell, no.

22:35.274 --> 22:37.541
You... you ain't got proof
that none of that happened.

22:37.543 --> 22:39.676
[Sniffs]

22:43.682 --> 22:46.316
Annie.

22:46.318 --> 22:48.485
Are you okay?

22:48.487 --> 22:49.486
Yeah.

22:49.488 --> 22:50.621
What happened?

22:50.623 --> 22:52.122
Your dumbass brother was selling drugs

22:52.124 --> 22:53.223
and almost got us killed.

22:53.225 --> 22:55.492
You are so twisted, girl!

22:55.494 --> 22:56.894
Is that why you need the money, J.B.?

22:56.896 --> 22:59.129
Oh, she is lying through
her teeth, Brody!

22:59.131 --> 23:00.664
You've always been trouble, J.B.

23:00.666 --> 23:03.567
[Cellphone rings]

23:05.171 --> 23:06.937
[Cellphone beeps]

23:06.939 --> 23:08.739
[Police radio chatter]

23:08.741 --> 23:10.040
Hey.

23:10.042 --> 23:11.975
- Frankie: Yeah.
- You can come back down.

23:11.977 --> 23:14.011
[Sighs] Okay, I'm just down the road.

23:14.013 --> 23:15.045
Okay.

23:15.047 --> 23:16.547
What happened?

23:16.549 --> 23:17.981
This is not about you.

23:17.983 --> 23:19.783
Okay, okay.

23:19.785 --> 23:21.084
All right, come on back down.

23:21.086 --> 23:22.186
Okay.

23:22.188 --> 23:24.788
Whoo! [Laughs]

23:24.790 --> 23:26.924
Well, you shouldn't have
stole my truck, Shelby.

23:26.926 --> 23:29.259
Well, I did, and I got $5,000 for it.

23:29.261 --> 23:31.995
You only... you only got $5,000 for it?

23:31.997 --> 23:34.431
You both know you're
admitting to crimes, right?

23:34.433 --> 23:35.866
You got how much for it?

23:37.770 --> 23:41.038
Where the hell did you
come from like a ghost?

23:41.040 --> 23:43.073
How much did you say you got for it?

23:43.075 --> 23:44.408
Rick. [Scoffs]

23:44.410 --> 23:45.576
You lied to me.

23:45.578 --> 23:47.411
You said you was buying scratch-offs.

23:47.413 --> 23:49.813
Well, I lied. Get over it.

23:49.815 --> 23:52.549
I tried to love you.

23:52.551 --> 23:55.152
Is he really doing this right now?

23:55.154 --> 23:57.354
Did you even share the rest
of the heroin with me?

23:58.991 --> 24:02.059
Am I not standing right here? Look!

24:02.061 --> 24:05.128
You used it all, Rick!
I didn't get any, remember?

24:05.130 --> 24:06.730
Just stop it, damn it! Stop it!

24:06.732 --> 24:08.432
Stupid son of a bitch.

24:08.434 --> 24:10.934
You're going to jail with me, J.B.

24:10.936 --> 24:13.537
They are lying.

24:13.539 --> 24:15.205
You're gonna come down to the station,

24:15.207 --> 24:16.440
and you're gonna tell me everything.

24:16.442 --> 24:17.941
Mobley, I didn't do
a damn thing, all right?

24:17.943 --> 24:20.577
Look, you're going, J.B.!
You need to tell me!

24:20.579 --> 24:23.747
These kind of people,
they always have other people.

24:23.749 --> 24:25.148
Damn it, Mobley.

24:25.150 --> 24:28.952
Who the hell shot at you, J.B.?!
Tell me!

24:31.290 --> 24:32.823
[Sniffs] All right, going to jail.

24:32.825 --> 24:35.592
Come on. Let's go. Wait.

24:35.594 --> 24:37.861
Who in the hell shot at those guys?

24:37.863 --> 24:39.930
A man came out of nowhere.

24:39.932 --> 24:42.499
Did you get a good look at him?

24:42.501 --> 24:43.667
No.

24:43.669 --> 24:45.969
I did.

24:45.971 --> 24:48.438
You recognize him?

24:48.440 --> 24:51.275
[Police radio chatter]

24:51.277 --> 24:52.776
No.

24:52.778 --> 24:54.945
No, I didn't.

24:57.850 --> 25:00.284
Deputy, take J.B. To the station.

25:00.286 --> 25:02.319
Yeah, I can drive myself.

25:02.321 --> 25:04.988
Follow him. Make sure
he goes right there.

25:04.990 --> 25:07.057
Hey, don't touch me, David.

25:07.059 --> 25:08.825
Go on, then.

25:08.827 --> 25:10.894
[Car door opens]
Bonnie.

25:10.896 --> 25:12.529
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

25:12.531 --> 25:14.598
Thanks for asking.
[Car door closes]

25:14.600 --> 25:16.033
Sheriff Mobley: This is just crazy.

25:16.035 --> 25:18.569
[Engine starts] All right, everybody!

25:18.571 --> 25:20.137
Go on back into your houses!

25:20.139 --> 25:22.539
There ain't nothing else to see now!

25:22.541 --> 25:24.341
We'll get this figured out soon enough.

25:24.343 --> 25:25.943
[Engine starts]
I'll tell you what happened.

25:25.945 --> 25:27.744
It's her! She's the reason!

25:27.746 --> 25:29.479
Rebel, get in the house right now.

25:29.481 --> 25:30.647
- No.
- I mean it.

25:30.649 --> 25:32.482
- Rebel, get in the house.
- Now.

25:32.484 --> 25:34.551
You bring trouble everywhere
you go, don't you?

25:34.553 --> 25:35.586
- Rebel, I mean it!
- Don't you?!

25:35.588 --> 25:37.754
Rebel, get in the damn house!

25:42.161 --> 25:46.363
Sheriff. Y'all need to do
something about this... right.

25:46.365 --> 25:47.364
[Sighs]

25:47.366 --> 25:49.266
Hey, Brody!

25:49.268 --> 25:52.502
Hey, Brody, come here.
Let me ask you something.

25:52.504 --> 25:54.571
Trying to get some information
about this... this one

25:54.573 --> 25:56.073
in number three here.

25:56.075 --> 25:59.242
You know, I ain't never seen
her give you no rent money.

25:59.244 --> 26:01.478
What you got going on
with her, Brody, huh?

26:01.480 --> 26:04.114
You need to get in the house.

26:04.116 --> 26:05.749
Your sister-in-law is something else.

26:05.751 --> 26:09.386
Yeah, I know. She works my nerves, too.

26:11.724 --> 26:15.292
And wait a minute. Why all the men
come running when she come around?

26:16.962 --> 26:19.896
She pays on time, all right?
I don't have to ask her.

26:19.898 --> 26:23.934
Oh, I think he talking
about you, Tavia.

26:23.936 --> 26:27.137
Look, she say she work in Riverbed,

26:27.139 --> 26:28.472
but I ain't never seen her.

26:28.474 --> 26:30.941
You need to mind your own
business and get in the house.

26:30.943 --> 26:33.977
Ooh, speaking of. Where you been?

26:33.979 --> 26:35.479
Excuse me?

26:35.481 --> 26:37.381
I seen you drive past.

26:37.383 --> 26:39.683
I had to go somewhere.

26:39.685 --> 26:41.618
And where you work again?

26:41.620 --> 26:43.420
- And who are you?
- Excuse me?

26:43.422 --> 26:44.755
What are you? The neighborhood watch?

26:44.757 --> 26:47.524
No, but I'm trying to figure out
who the hell you are.

26:47.526 --> 26:50.827
When I first met you,
I said my name was Frankie.

26:50.829 --> 26:52.963
Yeah, that's what you say.

26:52.965 --> 26:55.832
But you know we got the
internet around here.

26:56.814 --> 26:59.181
Go on inside, Frankie.

26:59.183 --> 27:00.916
Thank you.

27:01.276 --> 27:02.709
I'm watching you.

27:02.710 --> 27:04.443
Yeah, and I feel safe.

27:04.444 --> 27:06.277
You should.

27:07.851 --> 27:09.784
[insects chirping]

27:14.760 --> 27:16.693
[Door opens]

27:18.236 --> 27:20.102
Where have you been?

27:24.242 --> 27:27.710
Valerie, can you get Victor
some water, please?

27:28.980 --> 27:30.279
Yeah, sure.

27:30.281 --> 27:31.781
Thank you.

27:36.554 --> 27:38.187
Hey.

27:38.189 --> 27:40.756
Hey, baby. You're awake.

27:40.758 --> 27:42.258
Yeah.

27:42.260 --> 27:44.293
How do you feel?

27:44.295 --> 27:47.230
I'm still in a lot of pain.

27:50.368 --> 27:52.134
Thank you for coming.

27:52.136 --> 27:54.136
Of course.

27:58.676 --> 28:01.744
No one's ever loved me
as much as you do, Dax.

28:01.746 --> 28:03.412
Is that right?

28:03.414 --> 28:05.348
Yeah.

28:06.451 --> 28:09.385
Not even your mother or your father?

28:09.387 --> 28:11.988
[Chuckles] Baby.

28:11.990 --> 28:13.923
That's different.

28:13.925 --> 28:15.691
Yeah.

28:15.693 --> 28:18.461
I know it is.

28:18.463 --> 28:20.997
I love you.

28:20.999 --> 28:24.000
♪♪

28:30.608 --> 28:32.842
And you love them.

28:35.880 --> 28:37.313
Yes.

28:37.315 --> 28:39.482
Very much.

28:39.484 --> 28:41.517
[Cellphone rings]

28:41.519 --> 28:43.619
[Sniffs]

28:43.621 --> 28:45.054
[Cellphone beeps]

28:47.058 --> 28:48.658
Hello?

28:49.661 --> 28:51.761
Yeah. Yeah.

28:53.798 --> 28:55.932
You have a phone call.

28:57.035 --> 28:58.834
Who is it?

28:58.836 --> 29:00.670
Your sister.

29:03.942 --> 29:05.141
You didn't tell her that...

29:05.143 --> 29:07.276
- No. No.
- [Sighs]

29:12.717 --> 29:14.717
_

29:17.805 --> 29:19.805
_

29:19.893 --> 29:21.893
_

29:22.256 --> 29:24.256
_

29:25.872 --> 29:27.872
_

29:29.030 --> 29:31.030
_

29:32.212 --> 29:34.212
_

29:34.213 --> 29:36.213
_

29:37.533 --> 29:39.533
_

29:41.593 --> 29:43.593
_

29:46.995 --> 29:48.227
What happened, Victor?

29:48.229 --> 29:49.929
[Cellphone beeps]

29:49.931 --> 29:51.297
Dax.

29:51.299 --> 29:52.598
Yeah?

29:53.702 --> 29:55.835
My mother's been deported.

29:55.837 --> 29:57.437
What?

29:57.439 --> 30:00.640
She's been in this country for 15 years.

30:00.642 --> 30:02.208
Wow.

30:02.210 --> 30:04.110
"Wow"?

30:04.112 --> 30:05.578
Yeah.

30:06.581 --> 30:08.114
What?

30:12.354 --> 30:14.854
What did you do?

30:16.858 --> 30:19.192
Can I have my phone, please?

30:27.102 --> 30:30.103
The question is...

30:30.105 --> 30:32.505
What did you do?

30:32.507 --> 30:34.173
[Screaming]

30:34.175 --> 30:35.575
You have been...

30:35.577 --> 30:36.709
[Screaming]

30:36.711 --> 30:39.245
Dax, stop! Stop it! Stop it!

30:39.247 --> 30:40.513
Move!

30:40.515 --> 30:42.014
J.B.! J.B.!

30:42.016 --> 30:43.950
I won't let you hurt him!
Don't you hurt him!

30:43.952 --> 30:45.151
Get off of me, old man! Stop it!

30:45.153 --> 30:46.152
Stop! You stop it!

30:46.154 --> 30:48.020
You stop it right now, J.B.!

30:48.022 --> 30:49.122
What is going on?!

30:49.124 --> 30:50.790
He cheated on me!

30:50.792 --> 30:52.925
- What?!
- He can't cheat on you!

30:52.927 --> 30:54.627
He's a guy!

30:57.465 --> 30:58.965
A man!

31:02.804 --> 31:05.037
So...

31:05.039 --> 31:08.741
Your mother is on the next plane
back to the Dominican Republic.

31:08.743 --> 31:12.078
And your father is on the plane
right after that to El Salvador.

31:12.080 --> 31:15.681
And it's gonna take those planes
a long time to take off, Victor,

31:15.683 --> 31:17.683
because they're gonna
be in red-tape hell

31:17.685 --> 31:19.285
for quite some time,

31:19.287 --> 31:22.054
and you have yourself to thank for that.

31:23.558 --> 31:25.858
Dax, please.

31:25.860 --> 31:28.227
Now you beg.

31:28.229 --> 31:29.862
Aww.

31:29.864 --> 31:31.564
Please.

31:31.566 --> 31:33.065
And don't worry.

31:33.067 --> 31:35.368
Immigration will be here
within the next 24 hours

31:35.370 --> 31:37.804
to get you, too.

31:37.806 --> 31:40.273
No, Dax.

31:40.275 --> 31:42.175
Please, no. No, Dax!

31:42.177 --> 31:43.176
Dax!

31:43.178 --> 31:44.177
Dax.

31:44.179 --> 31:45.812
Dax!

31:45.814 --> 31:48.581
[Sobs]

31:52.487 --> 31:55.321
[Insects chirping]

31:55.323 --> 31:57.723
[Sighs]

31:57.725 --> 31:59.625
[Inhales sharply]

31:59.627 --> 32:01.260
- [Sighs]
- Are you okay?

32:01.262 --> 32:04.263
Yeah, just my... my stomach's
just been in knots

32:04.265 --> 32:06.232
since all this happened.

32:06.234 --> 32:08.334
I'm worried about you, Annie.

32:11.606 --> 32:13.506
Maybe you should be
worried about Bonnie.

32:13.508 --> 32:16.175
I am, all right?

32:16.177 --> 32:17.877
But Bonnie is tough.

32:17.879 --> 32:20.313
You and I both know
she takes care of the world.

32:20.315 --> 32:22.582
She's not into being looked after.

32:24.018 --> 32:25.751
Oh, and I am?

32:25.753 --> 32:28.020
You always let me.

32:28.022 --> 32:31.290
You know I'm not the same girl
that left this trailer park.

32:31.292 --> 32:33.993
And I'm not the same man that you left.

32:36.264 --> 32:38.397
Yeah, I can see that.

32:39.767 --> 32:41.767
Look, I just want to
make sure you're okay.

32:41.769 --> 32:43.402
That's all.

32:43.404 --> 32:45.505
I am.

32:46.608 --> 32:48.407
Okay. I got to go inside.

32:48.409 --> 32:50.309
Yeah.

32:50.311 --> 32:52.211
Yeah, okay.

32:52.213 --> 32:54.180
Hey, Bonnie!

32:55.583 --> 32:56.649
Yep?

32:56.651 --> 32:58.217
- Are you all right?
- Yeah.

32:58.219 --> 33:00.653
I just want to say thanks
again for stopping by.

33:00.655 --> 33:02.188
I'll talk to you later, okay?

33:02.190 --> 33:04.423
- Wait.
- Yeah?

33:04.425 --> 33:06.158
Come here. Talk to me.

33:06.160 --> 33:07.994
Um...

33:10.565 --> 33:11.564
Come here.

33:11.566 --> 33:14.500
♪♪

33:19.908 --> 33:21.274
What?

33:22.777 --> 33:24.043
You okay?

33:24.045 --> 33:26.445
Why do you keep asking me that?

33:26.447 --> 33:28.548
I just want to know that you're okay.

33:29.884 --> 33:31.751
I'm fine.

33:31.753 --> 33:33.719
Anything else?

33:37.492 --> 33:39.125
What's going on?

33:42.096 --> 33:43.529
Nothing.

33:44.866 --> 33:46.532
Bonnie, what the hell is this?

33:51.940 --> 33:53.573
What do you want from me, huh?

33:55.677 --> 33:58.144
I'm not gonna do this with you.
I told you.

33:58.146 --> 34:00.580
You can't keep doing this to me, Bonnie.

34:01.883 --> 34:04.383
I swear I won't let you.

34:05.687 --> 34:07.787
We shouldn't have done what we did.

34:15.563 --> 34:16.728
[Door opens]

34:18.065 --> 34:20.565
[Sighs]

34:28.826 --> 34:30.926
Everybody all right?

34:30.928 --> 34:33.395
[Engine starts]

34:35.125 --> 34:36.592
Yeah.

34:36.594 --> 34:38.226
Yeah, except you're here.

34:39.697 --> 34:42.197
Rebel, I'm tired of asking you.

34:42.199 --> 34:44.366
Stop it.

34:46.670 --> 34:48.337
Rebel.

34:50.241 --> 34:51.273
[Door slams]

34:51.274 --> 34:53.107
So you was out there talking to Brody?

34:53.108 --> 34:55.074
[Sighs] Don't start, Shelby.

34:55.076 --> 34:56.809
What? You upset he was with Annie?

34:56.810 --> 34:58.109
Enough! Please!

34:58.110 --> 35:00.010
When are you gonna grow up, Shelby?!

35:00.012 --> 35:02.079
Bonnie, he went right up
to her, hugged her first,

35:02.080 --> 35:03.946
didn't even ask about you.

35:03.947 --> 35:06.348
I want you to leave right now.

35:06.350 --> 35:08.283
Why?

35:08.285 --> 35:09.951
You told me you want me to stay here.

35:09.953 --> 35:11.920
That's when I thought
that you were in danger,

35:11.922 --> 35:15.223
and you're not, so I want
you to go right now!

35:16.360 --> 35:18.327
Fine. Fine, I'll go.

35:19.496 --> 35:21.930
But I know you.

35:21.932 --> 35:25.133
♪ Brody and Annie sitting in a tree ♪

35:25.135 --> 35:28.170
♪ k-i-s-s-i-n-g ♪

35:29.807 --> 35:30.806
[Door slams]

35:30.808 --> 35:32.974
[Vomits]

35:32.976 --> 35:35.344
[Groans, sighs]

35:35.346 --> 35:36.845
Bonnie: Hey, Annie.

35:36.847 --> 35:40.549
There's something for your
stomach under the counter.

35:40.551 --> 35:41.817
Okay.

35:41.819 --> 35:43.418
You'll feel better.

35:43.420 --> 35:45.020
[Sighs]

35:45.022 --> 35:47.122
[Toilet flushes]

35:47.124 --> 35:50.125
♪♪

36:04.742 --> 36:07.109
Hey. I'm about to go to sleep.

36:07.111 --> 36:08.944
I got to get up early.

36:08.946 --> 36:10.212
Okay.

36:10.214 --> 36:12.214
You talking to my brother?

36:12.216 --> 36:13.648
Yeah.

36:13.650 --> 36:15.150
Well, let me talk to him.
Let me tell him good night.

36:15.152 --> 36:17.285
No, no. I only got a little more
time left with him.

36:17.287 --> 36:19.187
Go on. Get.

36:19.189 --> 36:21.123
Okay, fine.

36:21.125 --> 36:23.692
Well, I love you, Nelson!

36:23.694 --> 36:26.294
All right, he said he love you, too.

36:31.869 --> 36:34.569
Yeah. Okay.

36:34.571 --> 36:38.006
As soon as she go to sleep,
I'll be right over, okay?

36:38.008 --> 36:39.808
All right.

36:39.810 --> 36:41.042
[Cellphone beeps]

36:41.044 --> 36:43.712
Annie: Damn.

36:43.714 --> 36:45.914
[Sighs]

36:50.687 --> 36:52.387
[Sniffs]

36:54.291 --> 36:55.791
Thanks for the medicine.

36:55.793 --> 36:57.159
Yeah, of course.

36:57.161 --> 36:58.794
[Sniffs]

36:58.796 --> 37:00.295
[Sighs]

37:00.297 --> 37:02.364
[Clears throat]

37:04.635 --> 37:07.068
So we gonna talk about it?

37:10.274 --> 37:12.607
Nothing to talk about, Annie.

37:16.113 --> 37:20.449
God, you know what bothers me
so much about this town?

37:20.451 --> 37:22.651
No one ever talks about their feelings.

37:24.721 --> 37:26.655
Annie, I'm fine.

37:26.657 --> 37:29.257
[Voice breaking] Well, I'm not.

37:29.259 --> 37:30.659
Why not?

37:30.661 --> 37:35.797
You should have told me
that you were with Brody.

37:38.669 --> 37:41.203
Yeah, I should've.

37:42.339 --> 37:43.939
But that's over, so...

37:43.941 --> 37:45.207
Is it?

37:45.209 --> 37:46.508
Yep.

37:49.112 --> 37:51.146
You're not acting like
it's over, Bonnie.

37:51.148 --> 37:53.248
[Chuckles] What are you talking about?

37:53.250 --> 37:54.616
What am I acting like, Annie?

37:54.618 --> 37:56.952
You seem upset, just like Shelby said.

37:56.954 --> 37:59.387
Shelby is a drug addict.

38:00.891 --> 38:03.158
Yeah, but she's telling the truth.

38:03.160 --> 38:04.826
[Scoffs]

38:04.828 --> 38:06.094
I don't care, Annie.

38:06.096 --> 38:07.829
- Do you love him?
- I really...

38:07.831 --> 38:10.165
No.

38:10.167 --> 38:12.067
Do you love him?

38:13.337 --> 38:14.803
I want you to drop it.

38:14.805 --> 38:16.872
You got to tell me, Bonnie.

38:16.874 --> 38:19.174
You got to tell me, okay?
I'm your sister.

38:21.178 --> 38:24.579
I don't love him. I never did.

38:24.581 --> 38:28.316
It was just something.
It was one thing that happened.

38:28.318 --> 38:30.318
Annie.

38:30.320 --> 38:32.053
[Sighs] Don't cry, all right?

38:32.055 --> 38:33.855
I want you to take my keys.

38:33.857 --> 38:35.991
Go over there if you want, all right?

38:35.993 --> 38:38.260
I'm gonna go to bed.

38:42.165 --> 38:43.598
Bonnie.

38:43.600 --> 38:45.500
Good night, Annie.

38:45.502 --> 38:48.336
[Sighs]

38:50.807 --> 38:53.108
[Dog barking in distance]

39:01.451 --> 39:04.452
♪♪

39:25.676 --> 39:27.309
[Knock on door]

39:27.311 --> 39:29.544
[Barking continues]

39:32.683 --> 39:35.050
[Car approaches]

39:41.925 --> 39:43.825
[Engine shuts off]

39:47.864 --> 39:48.997
Hi.

39:52.436 --> 39:54.402
Hey.

39:54.404 --> 39:56.004
I thought you were Bonnie.

39:57.808 --> 39:59.674
Yeah, you were probably
hoping it was her.

40:00.944 --> 40:03.378
It's always good to see you, Annie.

40:03.380 --> 40:05.280
What brings you by?

40:11.021 --> 40:13.088
I don't know.

40:15.626 --> 40:20.996
You know, so much has
changed about this place.

40:23.900 --> 40:26.234
Why didn't you tell me
you were with Bonnie?

40:29.906 --> 40:32.674
When would I have the
chance to tell you that?

40:32.676 --> 40:34.743
That's a good point.

40:36.179 --> 40:38.346
You never called me back.

40:38.348 --> 40:41.216
[Sighs]

40:41.218 --> 40:43.785
She doesn't care, Annie.

40:43.787 --> 40:45.286
You know she doesn't.

40:45.288 --> 40:46.821
Yeah, she does.

40:46.823 --> 40:49.624
No. She constantly pushes me away.

40:51.795 --> 40:53.828
But it's over now.

40:53.830 --> 40:56.831
♪♪

41:02.372 --> 41:04.673
You know...

41:04.675 --> 41:07.142
When I saw you...

41:08.879 --> 41:11.246
... it felt like no time
had passed at all.

41:14.518 --> 41:16.151
Make love to me.

41:16.153 --> 41:17.886
Please.

41:17.888 --> 41:19.521
Brody.

41:19.523 --> 41:21.022
We can't do this, Annie.

41:21.024 --> 41:22.524
Why not?

41:25.662 --> 41:27.462
Your sister.

41:27.464 --> 41:30.065
[Breathing heavily]

41:31.935 --> 41:33.835
You love her.

41:33.837 --> 41:35.637
[Sighs]

41:38.241 --> 41:39.674
Ma'am.

41:42.079 --> 41:44.412
You have a phone call.

41:45.482 --> 41:46.848
Ma'am.

41:49.886 --> 41:52.387
<i>Next on "Too Close to Home"... </i>

41:52.389 --> 41:53.955
You need to leave.

41:53.957 --> 41:55.090
You should take this call.

41:55.092 --> 41:56.791
Nelson: I was trying to find Regina.

41:56.793 --> 41:57.826
She... she ain't here.

41:57.828 --> 41:59.127
Well, where is she?

41:59.129 --> 42:00.462
Let's all laugh!

42:00.464 --> 42:02.197
Let's laugh at Bonnie and Brody!

42:02.199 --> 42:05.033
Let's laugh at me and Mac
having the same daddy.

42:05.035 --> 42:06.167
Where were you?

42:06.169 --> 42:07.769
Ain't your business, Tavia.

42:07.771 --> 42:10.605
You let me find out
you stepping out on him.

42:10.607 --> 42:12.474
Shelby: Look what I found.

42:12.476 --> 42:13.875
You got something you want to say?

42:13.877 --> 42:14.876
Who the hell's is it?

42:14.878 --> 42:16.344
Can you give me a ride?

42:16.346 --> 42:20.115
You... you know that queer who
got his ass kicked at the bar?

